"script": "Here's a secret hiding in your mouth right now: chewing gum is basically rubber. You see, the chewy base is made from synthetic polymers, the same family of materials used in plastics and glue. Then this base is heated until it melts into a thick, stretchy goo. Next, sweeteners, softeners, and flavors are folded in, and the mixture is rolled flat into long sheets. And this is exactly why gum never dissolves, no matter how long you chew. Finally, it's cut, dusted with powder, and wrapped, ready to be chewed forever and never swallowed.",
